The paper discusses the development of an analytical model to estimate the maximum operational range achievable by a mobile robot operating on a single battery discharge. This involves analyzing the energy utilization for various components mounted on the robot, such as computation, communication, sensing, propulsion, and steering. The paper also includes experiments with real robots on planar and graded surfaces to evaluate the estimation error for each case. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves some aspects of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG), which are relevant to the development of autonomous robots.
